# Personal Video Messages

A post-round modal that plays a short personal video from the creator, targeted at specific users (top players, loyal users, high-value churned users). Shown once per user, as a surprise-and-delight moment.

## Goal

Turn loyal and power users into genuine evangelists by giving them an unexpected personal thank-you. A short video (15-30s) from Sam addressing them by name, thanking them for their play, and inviting them to chat or try the new daily run.

## UX

1. User completes a round (or a full game — decide which trigger)
2. If the account has `personalVideo` set and `personalVideoSeen` is false, show a modal
3. Modal displays: "A message for {username}" with the video autoplay
4. Video has audio (muted-by-default with unmute prompt, to respect autoplay policies)
5. Close button, and optional "Reply to Sam" CTA (links to Discord or contact email)
6. On close, flag `personalVideoSeen: true` on the account — never show again

## Data Model

Add fields to the `accounts` collection:

```js
{
  personalVideo: {
    url: "https://artifactguesser.com/personal/mekb.mp4",  // static asset
    caption: "A message for mekb",                          // shown in modal
    recordedAt: Date
  },
  personalVideoSeen: Boolean  // false or unset = not yet shown
}
```

## API

### POST /api/accounts/mark-video-seen
- Authenticated
- Sets `personalVideoSeen: true` on current user's account
- Fire-and-forget, no response body needed

### Admin: POST /api/admin/personal-video
- Admin-only
- Body: `{ accountId, url, caption }`
- Sets the `personalVideo` field on target account, clears `personalVideoSeen`

## Frontend

### `<PersonalVideoModal />`
- Mounted in the Layout (or game summary screen)
- Reads `user.personalVideo` and `user.personalVideoSeen` from useUser hook
- Renders a `<Dialog>` with:
  - Heading: video.caption
  - `<video>` element, autoplay, muted initially, controls visible
  - "Thanks!" button that closes and calls mark-video-seen
  - Optional "Reply to Sam on Discord" button linking to Discord invite

### Trigger Point
Show on **game summary mount** when a round is complete, only once per session to avoid annoyance. Only shows if the flag conditions are met.

## Video Hosting

Store videos as static files in `/public/personal/` or a CDN-backed path. Keep filenames predictable: `{username}.mp4` so Sam can match videos to users easily when uploading.

File size target: under 5MB each. MP4/H.264 for broad compatibility.

## Analytics

Emit events:
- `personal_video_shown` — when modal renders
- `personal_video_completed` — when video finishes
- `personal_video_dismissed` — if closed before completing
- `personal_video_reply_clicked` — if Discord CTA used

## Rollout

Phase 1 (manual, high-touch):
- Sam records videos for top 5-10 users (mekb, bananaburner, spleen, hellpancake, etc.)
- Admin endpoint used to attach videos to accounts
- Monitor analytics for reaction

Phase 2 (optional, if successful):
- Expand to more users (top 20, top 50)
- Consider templated approach if production becomes bottleneck

## Open Questions

- [ ] Trigger: after every round, or only after completing a full game (5 rounds)?
- [ ] Reply mechanism: Discord, email form, or just a closing message?
- [ ] Should logged-out users ever see a generic welcome video? (probably no — personal is the point)
- [ ] Re-show if user clears cookies / new device? (store seen state server-side on account, so no)
